{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KBh7GYqmkAY2GKsipbg1mW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build is green. Here's a summary of what the new harness does:\n\n**`h5_attr_iter_fuzzer`** targets the attribute iteration and data read surface:\n\n1. **File open**: writes fuzzer bytes to a temp file, opens it read-only with `H5Fopen`.\n2. **Object traversal**: `H5Ovisit3` recursively visits every object (groups, datasets, named types) in the file.\n3. **Attribute iteration (two code paths per object)**:\n   - **Path A — `H5Aiterate2`**: iterates all attributes in name order; the callback calls `H5Aopen` by the name the iterator provides, then reads it.\n   - **Path B — `H5Aopen_by_idx` loop**: iterates by creation-order index (falling back to name-order index if creation order isn't tracked), covering the by-index open path.\n4. **Per-attribute read (`read_attribute_data`)**: calls `H5Aget_type` + `H5Aget_space`, computes element count, allocates a properly-sized buffer with `calloc`, calls `H5Aread` using the file's own datatype (so HDF5 drives any conversion/vlen-string path), then calls `H5Treclaim` to release any VLen-managed heap memory before `free`-ing the buffer.\n5. **Safety caps**: ≤ 4096 elements, ≤ 32 MB total buffer, ≤ 64 attributes per object — prevents OOM while still exercising real conversion code."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":127,"cache_read_input_tokens":64270,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":127,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be3652af-fb85-42e7-b906-2c8c1c67ad95","uuid":"d102a25a-efb5-4e0d-a76c-221f8d7bcce2"}
